oai_dc:dc.dc:title: AFA Visits ... The Aviary of Walter Moe
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Jennings, Jerry
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Many aviculturists refer to theiraviary as a ''bird ranch'' or ''birdfarm:' While many of these are quitegenteel in nature, a few meet the conceptualconnotation implied in theword "farm:' A farm is typically aplace where agricultural practices areemployed to produce a crop, and itimplies a certain intensity of purpose.Nothing better describes the aviary ofWalter Moe, a finch farmer par excellance!Walter's aviary is geared solelytowards the production of finches ofa wide variety of species. Theseinclude most of the Australian grassfinches,as well as many differentAfrican estrildid finches such asPurple Grenadiers, Fire Finches, andthe Twinspots. Other unique speciesinclude the Parrot Finches, amongwhich are the Bamboo, Red Head, Tricolored,and Pintail Non-pareil.
